import numpy as np
df['windspeed'] = np.log(df['windspeed'].apply(lambda x: x+1))   #windspeed+1
df['casual'] = np.log(df['casual'].apply(lambda x: x+1))         
df['registered'] = np.log(df['registered'].apply(lambda x: x+1))
df['count'] = np.log(df['count'].apply(lambda x: x+1))

#7.1XY

df.drop(['year_month','date'],axis=1,inplace=True)      #
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split    
#, .
df.drop(['casual','registered'], axis=1, inplace=True)
x = df.drop(['count'], axis=1)
y = df['count']
#
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)

#7.2
from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge
#alpha, 1.
rd = Ridge(alpha=1)       #alpha
rd.fit(x_train, y_train)   #
print(rd.coef_)            #
print(rd.intercept_)        #


#7.3
alphas = 10**np.linspace(-5, 10, 500)    #-5-1050010alphas
betas = []                               #
for alpha in alphas:                   #500alpha
    rd = Ridge(alpha = alpha)
    rd.fit(x_train, y_train)
    betas.append(rd.coef_)
#
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
plt.plot(alphas, betas)       #alpha
plt.xscale('log')    #
#
plt.grid(True)
#
plt.axis('tight')
plt.title(r'$\alpha$$\beta$')  #
plt.xlabel(r'$\alpha$')     #x
plt.ylabel(r'$\beta$')      #y
plt.show()
#, alpha10^7.alpha=10^7. 
#, , : .
from sklearn.linear_model import RidgeCV
from sklearn import metrics
rd_cv = RidgeCV(alphas=alphas, cv=10, scoring='r2')   #
rd_cv.fit(x_train, y_train)
rd_cv.alpha_
#1847.281437099636, 
rd = Ridge(alpha=1847) #, fit_intercept=False
rd.fit(x_train, y_train)
print(rd.coef_)
print(rd.intercept_)

'''---------------------8.---------------------------------'''
from sklearn import metrics
from math import sqrt
#
y_train_pred = rd.predict(x_train)
y_test_pred = rd.predict(x_test)
#
 
y_train_rmse = sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred))
y_train_score = rd.score(x_train, y_train)
y_test_rmse = sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred))
y_test_score = rd.score(x_test, y_test)
print('RMSE: {0}, R: {1}'.format(y_train_rmse, y_train_score))
print('RMSE: {0}, R: {1}'.format(y_test_rmse, y_test_score))

'''========9.Lasso========'''
import numpy as np 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  # 
from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso,LassoCV,LassoLarsCV   # Lasso,LassoCValphaLassoLarsCValpha

#model = Lasso(alpha=0.01)  # alpha
# model = LassoCV()  # LassoCValphaalpha
model = LassoLarsCV()  # LassoLarsCValphaalpha
model.fit(x_train, y_train)   # 
print(':\n',model.coef_,model.intercept_)

print(':\n',model)
print('alpha',model.alpha_)  # LassoCVLassoLarsCV

# 
#
y_train_pred = model.predict(x_train)
y_test_pred = model.predict(x_test)
#
 
y_train_rmse = sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred))
y_train_score = model.score(x_train, y_train)
y_test_rmse = sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred))
y_test_score = model.score(x_test, y_test)
print('RMSE: {0}, R: {1}'.format(y_train_rmse, y_train_score))
print('RMSE: {0}, R: {1}'.format(y_test_rmse, y_test_score))
